<shrimp type="function" name="Specular" description="Computes specular light at surface" author="rconstruct">
	<input name="Cspec" description="Specular color" type="color" default="color(1)"/>
	<input name="Ks" description="Specular coefficient" type="float" default="1"/>
	<input name="norm" description="The surface normal" type="normal vector" default="normalize(N)"/>
	<input name="viewer" description="The viewer vector" type="normal vector" default="-normalize(I)"/>
	<input name="roughness" description="The specular roughness" type="float" default="0.3"/>
	<output name="Ci" description="The amount of diffuse light" type="color" />
	<code>
		aov_specularcolor += $(Cspec);
		aov_specular += $(Ks) * specular( $(norm), $(viewer), $(roughness) );
		$(Ci) = aov_specularcolor * aov_specular;
	</code>
<usage>Specular term, using specular() call. Note that what is a standard specular() might vary with the renderer you're using. The specular color value is passed to aov_specularcolor, while the specular value, to the aov_specular AOV presets.</usage>
</shrimp>
